<h2>Instructor</h2>

<a href=http://www.math.gatech.edu/~margalit target=danmargalit>Prof.  
Margalit</a>

<h2>Text</h2>

<i>Linear and Discrete Mathematics</i>, Special edition for the Georgia Institute of Technology, with excerpts taken from <i>Discrete Mathematics with Graph Theory</i>, Third edition, by Edgar G. Goodaire and Michael M. Parmenter and from <i>Elementary Linear Algebra with Applications</i>, Ninth edition, by Bernard Kolman and David R. Hill.
<p>

<img src=LDM.jpg>

<h2>Course Description</h2>

The basics of mathematical induction and recursively defined sequences; complexity and rates of growth; combinatorics, counting methods, and elementary probability; graph theory and graph algorithms; linear algebra; linear programming and the simplex method. 

<h2>Class Meetings</h2>

Tuesdays and Thursdays, 3:05-4:25 in Howey Physics Building, Room L2.

<h2>Office Hours</h2>

Tuesday and Wednesday from 1:00 to 2:00, and by appointment.  The TA 
office hours are as follows: Geehoon Hong, Tuesday 11-12, Skiles 146A; Yun 
Gong, Monday 11-12, Skiles 145; Ke Yin, Wednesday 3-4, Skiles 246.

